<br>
I dinged into 61 again because I had collected every spell except 61 pet.  I have epic, so yes he would help but it's not a game breaker.<br>
<br>
Positives:<br>
-I love the nuke<br>
-The focus items sell well in the bazaar, being able to focus my 61+ spells is nice.<br>
-I love the new pet weapons and armor, they do make a difference.  They also sell well in the bazaar.<br>
-New shielding buffs are very nice, I finally clear 2000 HP with standard gear, and my FR, CR are way higher.<br>
-Tanks love my new Damage shield, 45 damage is a ton.<br>
<br>
Negatives:<br>
-TONS of lost hunting grounds.  Sebilis is largely light blue until you go deep in at 61.  Karnors, forget it.  Velks, gone. Maidens eye, tons of light blues.  Ankheva tons of light blues now.  Fungus grove? Yep, there too.  Efreeti camp in Sol B (one of my personal favorites) All light blue.  Kael tons more light blues, and not easy mobs I might add for their level.  This is all JUST at level 61...  one ding and I lost probably 40+ zones and more I'm still discovering.<br>
Basically, most of this game content was created around the fact that level 60 was the top, put some thought into that.  By leveling to 65 you gain FIVE player levels, but you lose TEN levels of mob exp.  Put some thought into that too.<br>
<br>
-PoP zones are already overcrowded, and it's going to get worse.  Nearly nothing else offers exp mobs or comparable exp per kill.  Verant fixed overcrowded zones by releasing expansions with tons of other zones to hunt in.  Now they are all crap to a level 65 player, so take a wild guess where those level 65 players are going to hang out.<br>
<br>
-Only level IV focus items work on 61+.  How many of you are decked out in IV focus items besides summoned ones?  I'm sorry you paid 50k or 50 raid points for that Frostweaver Dain's cloak, it's crap now.  Don't you feel good that a level 65 can still wear a flowing black sash and get hasted, but you can't wear that super UBER luclin drop and benefit from the focus effect at all?<br>
<br>
-If your going to level above 61, then you really want to get flagged or your hating life.  Get used to PoN, PoD, PoI, PoJ because it's about all you got until you get flagged after dinging 61.  I hope you enjoyed buying all those Everquest expansions with content most of you have never seen.  Because now its all crap.<br>
<br>
I'm totally unhappy being level 61 even though I have my spells.  I had WAY WAY more fun at level 60 and hunting anywhere I wanted. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Master Eandori Raintree<br>
